    <title type="text">Online Companion to Beginning Biblical Hebrew: A Grammar and Illustrated
      Reader (Baker Academic 2013)</title>
    <content type="html"><![CDATA[<div id="description"><a
      href="http://www.beginningbiblicalhebrew.com/" title="Beginning Biblical Hebrew">Beginning
      Biblical Hebrew</a>: A Grammar and Illustrated Reader </div><blockquote
      class="tr_bq"><div id="description"><span style="font-size: xx-small;"><img
      alt="http://assets.bakerpublishinggroup.com/processed/books/covers/listing/9780801048869.jpg"
      class="decoded" height="200"
      src="http://assets.bakerpublishinggroup.com/processed/books/covers/listing/9780801048869.jpg"
      width="154" /></span></div></blockquote><blockquote
      class="tr_bq"><span style="font-size: x-small;">This web site is for those actively or
      interested in teaching with our textbook, <strong><em>Beginning Biblical Hebrew: A
      Grammar and Illustrated Reader</em></strong> (Baker Academic
      2013).</span><br /><br /> <span style="font-size: x-small;">On this
      site we host a <a href="http://www.beginningbiblicalhebrew.com/bbh-blog/" target="_blank"
      title="BBH Blog"><strong>blog</strong></a>, in which we will address
      questions submitted by instructors or interested instructors, a <a
      href="http://www.beginningbiblicalhebrew.com/forum/bbh-instructor-forum/" target="_blank"
      title="BBH Instructor Forum"><strong>forum</strong></a>, in which we can
      interact dynamically with instructors using the textbook, a <a
      href="http://www.beginningbiblicalhebrew.com/bbh-resources/" target="_blank" title="BBH
      Resources – Beta"><strong>resource page</strong></a>, where we will post
      “beta” (in-progress, draft) supplementary materials to use with BBH (and we welcome
      suggestions!), and links to the <a
      href="http://www.beginningbiblicalhebrew.com/textbook-esources/" target="_blank"
      title="Textbook eSources"><strong>eSources</strong></a> that Baker has
      provided on their BBH textbook site.</span><br /> <span style="font-size:
      x-small;">Thank you for stopping by!</span><br /> <ul><li><span
      style="font-size: x-small;"><a href="http://www.beginningbiblicalhebrew.com/bbh-blog/"
      target="_blank" title="BBH Blog">Blog</a></span></li><li><span
      style="font-size: x-small;"><a
      href="http://www.beginningbiblicalhebrew.com/forum/bbh-instructor-forum/" target="_blank"
      title="BBH Instructor Forum">Forum</a></span></li><li><span
      style="font-size: x-small;"><a
      href="http://www.beginningbiblicalhebrew.com/bbh-resources/" target="_blank" title="BBH
      Resources –
      Beta">Beta&nbsp;Resources</a></span></li><li><span
      style="font-size: x-small;"><a
      href="http://www.beginningbiblicalhebrew.com/textbook-esources/" target="_blank"
      title="Textbook eSources">Textbook
      eSources</a></span></li></ul></blockquote><div
      id="description" style="text-align: center;">&nbsp;See also AWOL's list of <a
      href="http://ancientworldonline.blogspot.com/2009/09/open-access-textbooks.html">Open Access
      Textbooks and Language Primers</a></div>]]></content>
